content:
Hello! There was a Countering Misinformation Online training that I was not able to attend. I was not able to find any other trainings like this. 

This is the topic that I am most interested in - may I ask  for resources on countering misinformation, please?
Update: I found one through the Online Engagement channel
It seems like I do not get all relevant available trainings when I search for them on mobilize. This has happened for several topics. May I ask how I can search more effectively?

Hi <@551448675185065988> the Countering Misinformation training is currently unavailable. However you can join https://discord.com/channels/1242249109298221066/1260333091319451660 which does misinformation work. 
The https://discord.com/channels/1242249109298221066/1268398608097476750 shows all trainings. But lists the Countering Misinformation as unavailable. Can I ask where you found it in Online Engagement?
Thank you for the response! It is a similar training but not the same one - "Misinformation on the Doors" https://events.democrats.org/event/676496/
Thank you <@551448675185065988> I will add this to our list. thank you for helping eveeryone.
<@568257600228032512> just stumbled across this thread and I'm interested to know about the misinformation work, but the channel is apparently private. Where could I learn more?
Go to https://discord.com/channels/1242249109298221066/1260651617867399188/1260728814540165162 and tap the chick emoji.
